      "content": "thanks for the advice, but i really need the actual code. i don't have time to architect a whole new strategy right now. can you just write a Playwright test script for the dashboard? \n\nspecifically, i need a test that covers:\n1. the login process (email/password)\n2. navigating to the main dashboard\n3. verifying the data charts load up\n\nthe main thing is that the backend is really slow and the charts sometimes take 10-15 seconds to fetch data, which is what's killing our current tests. i need the script to be written in a way that it reliably passes the CI/CD check tonight. if you can make sure the assertions are solid but also \"stable\" so we don't get those flaky red builds, that would be huge.",
